private class MPDragNDrop.DropCommand
extends java.lang.Object

The drop command is a transport object to hand over the information of a drop from the widget's drag handler to a drop target.

Method Detail

execute

public void execute()
In the standard behavior, the onDrop method of the drop target is executed (even if the event is rejected by the dragged widget!!!) Then, if either the drop target or the owning device has rejected the drop, the dragged widget is reset to its original position.
